Use the standard library
This is how to monotonic of l:
   Remember that n is l's length
   When n is less than 2, then:
      The answer is 1
   End when
   Remember that up is 1
   Remember that down is 1
   Remember that i is 1
   Do this diff of n and 1 times:
      Remember that prev is item (diff of i and 1) in l
      Remember that curr is item i in l
      When curr is less than prev, then:
         Remember that up is 0
      End when
      When curr is more than prev, then:
         Remember that down is 0
      End when
      Increase i
   End do
   When up is 1, then:
      The answer is 1
   End when
   When down is 1, then:
      The answer is 1
   End when
   The answer is 0
Now you know
>>> monotonic of [1, 2, 4, 20] 
1
>>> monotonic of [1, 20, 4, 10] 
0
>>> monotonic of [4, 1, 0, -10] 
1